{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Refine"], "type": "title", "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "text": ["Increases the number of points/CVs in a curve or surface\nwithout changing its shape."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["You can localize the effect to a subsection of the input geometry."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["You can also use this node to decrease the number of points/CVs\nwithin a given tolerance, as a simplistic but fast method of\ndata reduction."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "text": ["Select the ", {"text": ["curves"], "fullpath": "/shelf/curve", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shelf/curve"}, " or surface to refine and press ", {"keys": ["Enter"], "text": null, "type": "keys"}, " to confirm your selection."]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "text": ["Click the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/refine", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SOP/refine"}, {"text": ["Refine"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/refine", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/refine"}, " tool on the ", {"text": ["Model"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."]}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["You can specify the amount of refinement in the ", {"text": ["parameter editor"], "fullpath": "/ref/panes/parms", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/ref/panes/parms"}, "."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/refine.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/refine.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Using Refine"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "includeme"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Refinement and unrefinement work both on faces (polygons, Bezier\n    curves and NURBS curves) and surfaces (primitive meshes, Bezier\n    surfaces and NURBS surfaces). To unrefine a face or a surface you\n    need to specify a parametric interval (not just a single value as in\n    refinement). This allows you to unrefine primitives within arbitrary\n    intervals, either locally or globally. For example, to unrefine the\n    whole primitive choose 0 and 1 as the two parametric boundaries;\n    ", {"text": ["[0,0.5]"], "type": "code"}, " will unrefine only the first parametric half of the\n    primitive."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["The interval boundaries are given by the First/Second U/V fields.\n    Since refinement does not need an interval, the Second U/V fields\n    are disabled by default."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["The Tolerance control is only available for unrefinement, and not\n    for refinement. Refinement does not need tolerances because it\n    generates a curve or a surface that is mathematically identical to\n    the original. Unrefinement, however, may tend to smooth out (or\n    \"melt\") the original in a given area. In short, unrefinement is\n    lossy; refinement isn\u2019t."]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["The Difference Between Refinement and Unrefinement"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Subset of geometry to refine."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Group"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Starting location in U ", {"text": ["[0,1]"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["First U"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/domainu1"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Ending location in U ", {"text": ["[0,1]"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Second U"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/domainu2"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Number of divisions to create in U."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["U Divisions"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/divsu"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Starting location in V ", {"text": ["[0,1]"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["First V"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/domainv1"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Ending location in V ", {"text": ["[0,1]"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Second V"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/domainv2"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Number of divisions to create in V."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["V Divisions"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/divsv"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["Number of knots to insert in each location /refinev when\n            refining NURBS geometry. /refineu"]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "text": ["NURBS Count U, V"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["Refine splines at equal intervals."]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "text": ["Uniform Domain Lengths"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["Each refinement is done at the center of the maximum knot\n            spans (splines) or edge length (polygons)."]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "text": ["Uniform Arc Lengths"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Refine"]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["Number of knots to remove from NURBS geometry at each\n            location. /unrefineu /unrefinev"]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "text": ["NURBS Count U, V"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["Only remove knots that do not change the /tolu resulting\n            shape by more than this distance. /tolv"]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "text": ["NURBS Tolerance U, V"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Unrefine"]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["Divides splines at equal intervals."]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "text": ["Uniform Domain Lengths"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["Each divide is done at the center of the maximum knot spans\n            (splines) or edge length (polygons)."]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "text": ["Uniform Arc Lengths"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Subdivide"]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/resample", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/resample"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/convert", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/convert"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/carve", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/carve"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "title", "text": ["BasicRefine"]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["This example contains a few methods of how the Refine SOP can be used to add or remove detail from many types of surfaces."]}], "text": "BasicRefine", "type": "load_example", "attrs": {"path": "/examples/nodes/sop/refine/BasicRefine", "examplefile": "/examples/nodes/sop/refine/BasicRefine.otl", "examplefor": "/nodes/sop/refine"}}], "usages": [{"body": [{"ref": "/examples/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject/ShatterGlass", "type": "include"}], "text": "ShatterGlass", "type": "load_example", "attrs": {"path": "/examples/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject/ShatterGlass", "examplefile": "/examples/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject/ShatterGlass.otl", "examplefor": "/nodes/dop/rbdglueobject"}}, {"body": [{"ref": "/examples/nodes/sop/refine/BasicRefine", "type": "include"}], "text": "BasicRefine", "type": "load_example", "attrs": {"path": "/examples/nodes/sop/refine/BasicRefine", "examplefile": "/examples/nodes/sop/refine/BasicRefine.otl", "examplefor": "/nodes/sop/refine"}}], "container": true, "level": 1, "text": "Examples", "role": "section", "type": "examples_section", "id": "examples"}], "title": ["Refine"], "summary": ["Increases the number of points/CVs in a curve or surface\nwithout changing its shape."], "attrs": {"version": null, "tags": "polygons, splines, topology, model", "namespace": null, "internal": "refine", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "SOP/refine"}, "included": ["/shelf/refine", "/examples/nodes/sop/refine/BasicRefine"], "type": "root"}